# CLAUDE.md

<!-- One paragraph: what is this repo, who works in it, in what order -->
## What This Repo Is

A REST API for a bookstore, built with FastAPI + PostgreSQL.

<!-- Commands a linter/README won't surface, e.g. non-default test invocations -->
## Commands

```bash
make dev        # starts API + DB via docker-compose
make test        # runs pytest against a throwaway test DB
```

<!-- Anything Claude would otherwise have to rediscover by reading every file -->
## Conventions

- Endpoints live in `app/routers/`, one file per resource
- Every endpoint needs a Pydantic response model — no raw dicts

<!-- Directories that look editable but aren't — saves a wasted round-trip -->
## Do Not Touch

- `migrations/` — generated by Alembic, hand-editing breaks the migration graph
- `vendor/` — vendored third-party code, patch upstream instead

<!-- Git/PR conventions specific to this team, not derivable from git log -->
## Git Conventions

- Branch from `main`: `feature/<name>` or `fix/<name>`
- Commit format: `type: short description`
